Specimens collected in Java of brown color. Male cerci not very stout at base, narrow apical area moderately curved with internal apical tooth larger and stouter than pre-apical tooth. Subgenital plate with moderately long styli (longer than in “P. Ratu green“ =
M. himalaya
).

Literature data on song: Korsunoskaya 2008 (
CAMBODIA
)
